Arko Pravo Mukherjee (born 19 May 1983), better known by the mononym Arko, is an Indian singer-songwriter and music composer who has worked in the Bollywood film industry since 2012.
Arko Pravo Mukherjee was born on 19 May 1983 in a Bengali Brahmin  family to Apurba Kumar Mukherjee and Mahasweta Mukherjee in Kolkata, West Bengal.
Arko graduated with an MBBS medical degree in 2007 from Burdwan Medical College.
He completed his internship at Calcutta Medical College and then in 2008 he shifted to Mumbai to pursue a career in Bollywood film industry as a music director, singer songwriter.
In 2012, Arko debuted as a music composer in Jism 2.
In 2014, he composed two songs for Yaariyan for which he earned a nomination of Filmfare Award for Best Music Director along with Pritam, Mithoon, Yo Yo Honey Singh and Anupam Amod.
In the same year, he composed songs for Hate Story 2, Tamanchey and The Shaukeens.
In 2015, he composed for Kuch Kuch Locha Hai, Bhaag Johnny, Jazbaa.
In 2016, he composed a song for Kapoor & Sons and Baar Baar Dekho.
He earned another nomination of Filmfare Award for Best Music Director for Kapoor & Sons along with Amaal Mallik, Badshah, Tanishk Bagchi, Benny Dayal & Nucleya.
In 2017, he composed for Sweetiee Weds NRI, Dobaara: See Your Evil, Laali Ki
In 2017, he composed for Sweetiee Weds NRI, Dobaara: See Your Evil, Laali Ki
In 2018, Arko composed a song for Hate Story 4 and a song for Baaghi 2.

Arko was the playback singer for the first time in "Saathi Re" for Kapoor & Sons following Rustom, Baar Baar Dekho, Laali Ki Shaadi Mein Laaddoo Deewana, Tum Bin II, Sweetiee Weds NRI, Dobaara: See Your Evil, Bareilly Ki Barfi, Daas Dev and a single titled "Aainda".
Best Debut Music 2012 – Stardust (Jism 2)
Best Debut Lyrics 2012 – Stardust (Jism 2)
Best Sufi song 2012 – GIMA
Best debut Music Director 2013 – GIMA
Best Lyrics 2013 – GIMA
Best Music 2014 for Yaariyan – nominated at Filmfare Awards, IIFA awards, Screen Awards etc.
Awarded TIFFA – Best Music Director ( Song Of the Year – Tere Sang yaara )
Mirchi Music Awards 2020 Album Of The Year Kesari
Mirchi Music Awards 2020 Album Of The Year Kesari
